    {
      "id": "c798b58007ffa098d5365f20cd6e5429aac92d0f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2014-05-26 07:16:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nI'd hope we could solve this problem moving mdt_rename_sanity() into MDD, but I'd like to clarify this with Di.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "49312e8a8c74873d69a937ef40aac9cea1fb2b8c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-05-26 09:52:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.5/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/524f2014-e4ba-11e3-bb3a-52540035b04c).  Ran 19 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "15bd22f697e7978b898a42c259d86e4e0ca0163b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2014-05-26 12:21:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nmy understanding is that the original mdt_rename_sanity() was implemented in MDT due to the original structuring where MDD was a local service and basically couldn't access remote storage. this isn't a problem any more and I'd think it's better from layering point of view to have this check in MDD - this check is an implementation detail of POSIX namespace which is implemented in MDD.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "1590244641c744ef8f5bf8ee31c8b87ec6640a35",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-05-26 18:13:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAlex: I agree with you about moving rename sanity check to MDD. But it seems to me, mdt_rename_sanity is being used to sort out parent/child relationship for ldlm locking? Though this function name should be changed to a better one, IMHO.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "09c1d8c1fcc7d54618664a7ee76ea568a6acd931",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-05-26 18:31:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAlex, does this restructuring need to be done for 2.6 or could this patch land to fix the problem that is being hit and do the MDT->MDD cleanup in 2.7?  Alternately, would you be able to refresh this patch to implement the code the way you want it?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "e36af847cbdf7776f9c2f380b231115c1ce00939",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2014-05-26 19:20:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIMO, there are still missing bits in the big picture. e.g. mdt_rename_sanity() is called from mdt_rename_parents_lock() as well. and given mdt_reint_rename_or_migrate() grabs the global lock at the beginning of rename, why do we need to call mdt_rename_sanity() directly from mdt_reint_rename_internal() ? once the global lock is taken, no changes to the hierarchy is possible, so the first  mdt_rename_sanity() should be enough?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "53ff6a8fecc139fc08d19aeef087f334a8a59e80",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 135,
        "name": "Vitaly Fertman",
        "email": "vitaly.fertman@hpe.com",
        "username": "vitaly_fertman"
      },
      "date": "2014-05-27 10:41:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nno enough. global lock does not let to race with another rename. we race with unlinks here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "eb32233f0b72b6369a94c37a6f03dc8564cbeeb5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
